669\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 14, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104irg1665702783697.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/irg1665702783697.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/irg1665702783697.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"irg1665702783697\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The <span class=\"keyword apiname\">uniface.ValidationError</span> object provides access to the error number and message of a validation error on the server. It is returned by the <span class=\"keyword apiname\">FieldErrorContext.getError</span> function when used in the showError and <span class=\"keyword apiname\">clearError</span> web triggers.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"irg1665702783697__section_q4z_2gc_dwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d424913e58\">Syntax Error Properties</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"irg1665702783697__table_d15251e1_d15252e1_d15253e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"irg1665702783697__table_d15251e1_d15252e1_d15253e1__entry__1\"> Property Name </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"irg1665702783697__table_d15251e1_d15252e1_d15253e1__entry__2\"> Description </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"irg1665702783697__table_d15251e1_d15252e1_d15253e1__entry__1\"> message </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"irg1665702783697__table_d15251e1_d15252e1_d15253e1__entry__2\"> Validation error message. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"irg1665702783697__table_d15251e1_d15252e1_d15253e1__entry__1\"> valueInError </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"irg1665702783697__table_d15251e1_d15252e1_d15253e1__entry__2\"> Field value that caused the validation error.\n              </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"irg1665702783697__section_kkw_jgc_dwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d424913e107\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"irg1665702783697__p_d127619e1_d127620e1_d127621e1\">A <span class=\"keyword apiname\">uniface.ValidationError</span> object is\n        generated when validation fails on the server after data has been submitted from the\n        client.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"irg1665702783697__p_d127622e1_d127623e1_d127624e1\">You can access the properties of the\n          <span class=\"keyword apiname\">uniface.ValidationError</span> using the <span class=\"keyword apiname\">getError</span> function\n        of the field. </p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"irg1665702783697__section_rzb_z5v_1dc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d424913e128\">Example: Using uniface.ValidationError </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"irg1665702783697__p_d127628e1_d127629e1_d127630e1\">For example, in the following code, the showError web\n        trigger is used to display an alert box with the information about the error.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">The example performs the following:</p>\n<ol class=\"ol\" id=\"irg1665702783697__ol_ps2_ngc_dwb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"irg1665702783697__li_d46295e1_d46296e1_d46297e1\">Gets the <span class=\"keyword apiname\">ValidationError</span> object\n          using the field's <span class=\"keyword apiname\">getError</span> function. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"irg1665702783697__li_d46298e1_d46299e1_d46300e1\">Extracts the elements of the error object and put\n          them into the variable <code class=\"ph codeph\">vErrorString</code>. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"irg1665702783697__li_d46301e1_d46302e1_d46303e1\">Displays an alert with contents of the\n            <code class=\"ph codeph\">vErrorString</code> variable. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"irg1665702783697__li_d46304e1_d46305e1_d46306e1\">Returns <code class=\"ph codeph\">true</code> to enable the default\n          Uniface error handling. </li>\n</ol>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104irg1665702783697_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"irg1665702783697__codeblock_xmf_pgc_dwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">webtrigger showError \n javascript\n // this = the current FieldErrorContext object\n var vErrorObject = this.getError(); <a class=\"xref\" href=\"#irg1665702783697__li_d46295e1_d46296e1_d46297e1\">1</a>\n var vErrorString = \"There is a Validation Error./n/n\"; <a class=\"xref\" href=\"#irg1665702783697__li_d46298e1_d46299e1_d46300e1\">2</a>\n vErrorString += \"Value in error: \" + vErrorObject.valueInError+ \"/n/n\"; \n alert(vErrorString); // Show error alert box  <a class=\"xref\" href=\"#irg1665702783697__li_d46301e1_d46302e1_d46303e1\">3</a>\n endjavascript\n \n return true   <a class=\"xref\" href=\"#irg1665702783697__li_d46304e1_d46305e1_d46306e1\">4</a>\n \nend</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zkz1665702538660.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>getError()</a><p>Returns an error object for the field, if a syntax error or validation error occurred.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/aqh1665702590886.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Syntax Checking in Dynamic Server Pages</a><p>Uniface always performs server-side syntax checks when data in a dynamic server page (DSP) is validated or stored. It is also possible to perform browser-side syntax checks, so that errors are flagged before incorrect data is submitted to the server.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dcx1665702590735.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>webtrigger onSyntaxError</a><p>The onSyntaxError web trigger is activated when a field syntax violation is detected in the browser. It can be used to customize or override the default syntax error handling.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/uuy1665702590810.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>webtrigger onSyntaxErrorResolved</a><p>The onSyntaxErrorResolved web trigger is used to customize behavior when a field syntax error has been corrected.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528669\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528669\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "uniface.ValidationError Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 14, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 The uniface.ValidationError object provides access to the error number and message of a validation error on the server. It is returned by the FieldErrorContext.getError function when used in the showError and clearError web triggers. Syntax Error Properties Property Name Description message Validation error message. valueInError Field value that caused the validation error. Description A uniface.ValidationError object is generated when validation fails on the server after data has been submitted from the client. You can access the properties of the uniface.ValidationError using the getError function of the field. Example: Using uniface.ValidationError For example, in the following code, the showError web trigger is used to display an alert box with the information about the error. The example performs the following: Gets the ValidationError object using the field's getError function. Extracts the elements of the error object and put them into the variable vErrorString . Displays an alert with contents of the vErrorString variable. Returns true to enable the default Uniface error handling. Explain this code webtrigger showError javascript // this = the current FieldErrorContext object var vErrorObject = this.getError(); 1 var vErrorString = \"There is a Validation Error./n/n\"; 2 vErrorString += \"Value in error: \" + vErrorObject.valueInError+ \"/n/n\"; alert(vErrorString); // Show error alert box 3 endjavascript return true 4 end Copy Related Links getError() Returns an error object for the field, if a syntax error or validation error occurred. Syntax Checking in Dynamic Server Pages Uniface always performs server-side syntax checks when data in a dynamic server page (DSP) is validated or stored. It is also possible to perform browser-side syntax checks, so that errors are flagged before incorrect data is submitted to the server. webtrigger onSyntaxError The onSyntaxError web trigger is activated when a field syntax violation is detected in the browser. It can be used to customize or override the default syntax error handling. webtrigger onSyntaxErrorResolved The onSyntaxErrorResolved web trigger is used to customize behavior when a field syntax error has been corrected. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}